    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="155"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Kreismann</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 24, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatch of September 7, No. 29, has been
                    received. I shall receive with much pleasure your promised paper on the commerce
                    and revenue of Prussia.</p>
                <pb facs="0219" n="195" xml:id="pg_195"/>
                <p>Recent military and political events Lave probably wrought a change in opinion in
                    Berlin concerning the prospects of the United States since your despatch was
                    written. No class of men pronounce themselves upon political questions more
                    confidently than courtiers and placemen, and yet no class of men so habitually
                    judge more erroneously. They study the signs, not the causes, of social
                    movements.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hermann Kreismann</hi>, &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.,
                            &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi
                            rend="italic">, Berlin.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
